Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.02,0:00:08.32,Onscreen_Text,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(198,195)}Skill Crystal\NRabbit
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.17,0:00:10.88,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,A Skill Crystal...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.16,0:00:16.77,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,It probably allows you to \Ncreate an item with a skill
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.28,0:00:20.54,Status Text,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(140,63)\fs12\fscy140}Identify
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.28,0:00:20.54,Status Text,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs12\fscy130\pos(110,115)}Scimitar
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.28,0:00:20.54,Status Text,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fs20\pos(330,168)\1a&H20&}Skill Slot\NEmpty
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.77,0:00:19.98,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,when you combine it with an empty skill slot.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.23,0:00:25.15,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,The problem is finding a dwarf with \Nthe dwarf-specific Blacksmith job.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.98,0:00:28.95,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Now how am I going to find one?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.55,0:00:32.30,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,I'm ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.96,0:00:35.42,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for making you do it yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.42,0:00:36.26,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.14,0:00:42.72,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Cooking is supposed to be my job.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.72,0:00:45.09,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,You shouldn't have to help me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.09,0:00:47.77,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,We can have that conversation another time.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.10,0:00:50.52,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Our food will get cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.72,0:00:54.04,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.33,0:01:05.12,Sign_Basic,ShowTitle,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1500,0)\fnTimes New Roman\b1\c&H8A0001&\bord3\3c&HFFFFFF&\blur3\shad0\fs30\fscy150}in the Labyrinth of Another World
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.87,0:01:05.12,Sign_Basic,ShowTitle,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1075,0)\pos(320,10)\bord3\an8\fnTimes New Roman\b1\fs44\fsp10\shad0\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H2281EA&\blur3}H{\3c&H3463E2&}a{\3c&H4546D9&}r{\3c&H5728D1&}e{\3c&H680AC8&}m
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.80,0:02:27.75,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.31,0:02:31.00,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,But it was green until recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.00,0:02:33.38,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably because I merged \Ntwo crystals recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.38,0:02:34.43,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.43,0:02:36.16,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.87,0:02:41.01,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,You said yellow Magic Crystals can \Nbe sold for 100 thousand nars, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.62,0:02:43.51,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.84,0:02:46.52,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Then we'll have the money we need.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.11,0:02:49.39,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Roxanne, change of plans.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.84,0:02:51.84,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go to Vale after this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.84,0:02:53.43,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have business there?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.43,0:02:54.82,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to pay a visit to Alan.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.20,0:02:58.06,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,I want to write a will.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.23,0:03:01.88,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,A will?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.88,0:03:03.78,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Don't make that face.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.36,0:03:07.29,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,I realized something after \Nthat incident the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.71,0:03:11.79,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,I should be prepared to die \Nif I'm entering labyrinths.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.12,0:03:13.98,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Normally when a master dies,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.98,0:03:16.30,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,their slaves join them in death, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.48,0:03:24.80,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to be freed when I die.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.88,0:03:29.96,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,I appreciate that, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.14,0:03:37.65,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,If you trust me, \Nthen please don't write a will.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.89,0:03:38.52,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.96,0:03:42.61,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,I'll protect you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.96,0:03:44.53,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a warrior.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.20,0:03:47.44,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,If my master died,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.44,0:03:50.45,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't be able to \Ncontinue living in disgrace.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.39,0:03:54.10,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,She's not joking.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.55,0:03:59.35,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I depend on you, and I \Nunderstand what you're trying to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.35,0:04:02.68,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,But labyrinths aren't the \Nonly places I might die.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.28,0:04:05.96,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,I could even drop dead from an illness.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.42,0:04:09.15,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,I'd find a way to cure you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.15,0:04:12.25,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Um, are you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.25,0:04:13.01,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.85,0:04:17.54,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,She's actually for real.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.96,0:04:21.31,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,If you insist, then I won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.31,0:04:22.77,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.77,0:04:24.15,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.68,0:04:27.91,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Because you're a wonderful man.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.24,0:04:31.32,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,You're young, strong, and skilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.76,0:04:34.55,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you'll achieve great things.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.22,0:04:39.84,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,And on top of that, \Nyou've been nothing but kind to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.92,0:04:43.33,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,I must return the favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.25,0:04:52.30,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.50,0:04:56.56,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Roxanne called herself a warrior.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.56,0:04:59.69,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,She's like a loyal samurai willing \Nto sacrifice herself for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.93,0:05:03.54,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,I probably can't change her mind, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.16,0:05:05.60,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Let me say this, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.60,0:05:06.66,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.46,0:05:11.25,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,I probably won't achieve \Nanything significant.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.25,0:05:12.51,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,That's not...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.99,0:05:14.66,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.16,0:05:18.58,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,If anything, I'm here specifically \Nto achieve nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.40,0:05:21.30,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.86,0:05:23.64,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.64,0:05:25.72,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Just know that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.49,0:05:28.03,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.03,0:05:29.50,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,But we're still going to Vale.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.88,0:05:33.06,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,I've got other business with Alan.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.93,0:05:35.93,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,I realized during battle the other day that
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.36,0:05:39.31,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,it's time to think about expanding our party.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.60,0:05:40.62,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.52,0:05:45.82,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Monsters start appearing in groups \Nof four, starting on the eighth floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.18,0:05:48.84,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,If I'm going to be focusing on magic,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.84,0:05:50.74,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,then I'd like another front-line fighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.12,0:05:53.25,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Ideally, a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.25,0:05:56.20,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,No, they don't have to be a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.20,0:05:58.25,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,They don't have to be, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.23,0:06:02.71,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,So good. Who could deny the appeal of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.56,0:06:06.17,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.17,0:06:08.77,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What is it, Roxanne?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.77,0:06:12.64,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,I think recruiting more party \Nmembers is a good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.91,0:06:17.08,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Would it be all right if I accompanied \Nyou to Mr. Alan's mansion?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.08,0:06:18.64,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.10,0:06:22.01,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,If Roxanne is opposed to the idea,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.01,0:06:24.33,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,then I don't have to choose a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.90,0:06:27.65,Onscreen_Text,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(12,186)\an4\c&HFFFFFF&\fs36\shad0}Vale\NAlan's Mansion
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.60,0:06:27.65,Main,SERVANT,0000,0000,0000,,Please wait here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.23,0:06:30.62,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Roxanne, have a seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.62,0:06:32.39,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.39,0:06:35.76,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't sit, \Nhe'll think I'm back to sell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.76,0:06:37.62,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.18,0:06:45.46,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,Well, well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.98,0:06:48.97,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for coming, Mr. Michio.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.20,0:06:52.39,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for always dropping in out of the blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.39,0:06:54.91,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all. \NYou're welcome to come anytime.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.89,0:06:58.93,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,So, what can I do for you today?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.93,0:07:02.48,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm thinking about adding \Nanother party member.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.48,0:07:04.73,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,A good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.73,0:07:06.60,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to ask you something.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.60,0:07:09.17,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Would it be possible to \Npurchase a Blacksmith slave?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.63,0:07:13.36,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,A Blacksmith? You mean a dwarf.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.36,0:07:17.08,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's not impossible, but it is difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.74,0:07:20.80,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,Are you aware merging \NSkill Crystals often fails?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.80,0:07:21.71,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.71,0:07:24.06,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,Because those are so valuable,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.06,0:07:28.71,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,repeated failures can affect the \Nrelationship between a slave and their master.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.13,0:07:33.47,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's not uncommon for it to end \Nunfortunately for both parties.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.90,0:07:36.77,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,Because dwarves know that,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.77,0:07:39.79,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,they don't often become \Nslaves as Blacksmiths.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.79,0:07:40.85,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure they don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.26,0:07:44.77,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,As a result, there are \Nfew Blacksmith slaves,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.77,0:07:47.21,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,making them quite expensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.21,0:07:50.22,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,What about a dwarf who isn't a Blacksmith?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.22,0:07:53.40,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,Dwarves are a powerful people.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.40,0:07:55.41,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,They make excellent front-line fighters.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.76,0:07:58.76,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,If you're looking for new party members,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.76,0:08:00.27,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,a dwarf would be perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.27,0:08:00.87,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.56,0:08:04.67,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,Currently I have a single dwarf,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.95,0:08:09.55,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,but unfortunately, \Nher personality isn't suited to fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.55,0:08:12.97,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,"Her?" So she's a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.00,0:08:12.97,Main - Top,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,If you're determined to acquire a dwarf,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.97,0:08:16.93,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,I could write you a letter of \Nintroduction to another shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.93,0:08:19.52,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Well, what do you think, Roxanne?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.52,0:08:22.48,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Uh, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.86,0:08:28.27,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,As long as we're here, \Nwhy don't we meet the dwarf he has?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.54,0:08:32.52,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't like her, then you \Nsimply don't need to acquire her.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.52,0:08:35.67,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,I see. It's free to take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.67,0:08:36.96,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,You heard her.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.96,0:08:39.16,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Could you show us the dwarf?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.16,0:08:40.77,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.36,0:08:45.38,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have her get ready. \NWait here, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.00,0:08:49.26,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,So anyway, I bought a house in Quratar.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.26,0:08:51.27,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.64,0:08:53.43,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,Enter.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.69,0:08:59.39,Main,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,She's ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.27,0:09:06.60,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,That's the woman Roxanne \Nmentioned who treated her well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.60,0:09:08.22,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,Bring her here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.76,0:09:09.77,Main,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.89,0:09:18.74,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,This is the only dwarf I \Ncurrently have, Sherry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.36,0:09:25.00,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Sixteen years old?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.36,0:09:27.12,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,She's the same age as Roxanne.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.76,0:09:28.88,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,These ears...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.32,0:09:32.38,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,They look like elf ears, but I guess \Ndwarves have ears like these, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.06,0:09:35.20,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,He said dwarves are suited to front-line fighting,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.20,0:09:38.39,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,but she doesn't look particularly muscular.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.35,0:09:45.96,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,She seems like a short girl who's \Nfairly mature, slender, and cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.96,0:09:49.32,Main,SHERRY,0000,0000,0000,,U-Um, it's nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.08,0:09:53.39,Main,SHERRY,0000,0000,0000,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.27,0:10:01.41,Main,SHERRY,0000,0000,0000,,I'm already a level ten Explorer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.41,0:10:04.00,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, my Identify skill already told me that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.00,0:10:07.51,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,If you're an Explorer, then you won't \Nhave any problems entering labyrinths.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.51,0:10:10.14,Main,SHERRY,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, that's not what I meant.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.87,0:10:13.13,Main,SHERRY,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.12,0:10:19.13,Main,SHERRY,0000,0000,0000,,I failed to become a Blacksmith.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.04,0:10:21.58,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.58,0:10:24.12,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Do you mind if we have a seat \Nso I can ask her some questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.12,0:10:25.02,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.78,0:10:28.26,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, you failed?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.26,0:10:31.31,Main,SHERRY,0000,0000,0000,,Once dwarves become level ten Explorers,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.31,0:10:34.06,Main,SHERRY,0000,0000,0000,,they have the option to change \Ntheir job to Blacksmith.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.06,0:10:36.30,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,And you couldn't?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.78,0:10:37.71,Main,SHERRY,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.71,0:10:41.32,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,How is whether or not a dwarf can \Nbecome a Blacksmith determined?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.32,0:10:45.61,Main,SHERRY,0000,0000,0000,,Generally those who have an \Naptitude for exploring labyrinths
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.61,0:10:47.75,Main,SHERRY,0000,0000,0000,,can also become Blacksmiths.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.09,0:10:50.67,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, since she \Ncouldn't become a Blacksmith,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.67,0:10:54.10,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,she wouldn't be useful in labyrinths either.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.63,0:10:58.40,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,But is it really possible for a dwarf \Nto fail to become a Blacksmith
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.40,0:11:00.13,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,because they lack aptitude?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.52,0:11:03.64,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,In this world, jobs are learned.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.89,0:11:05.01,Status Text,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(80,8)\fs14\fscy140\1a&H20&\fsp1}Status
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.89,0:11:05.01,Status Text,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs12\fscy140\1a&H20&\pos(16,65)}Kaga Michio
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.89,0:11:05.01,Onscreen_Text,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs14\shad0\pos(268,250)}<Male 17 Years Old>\N Villager: Lv 1\N Thief: Lv 1\N Equipment: Sandals
Dialogue: 1,0:11:04.19,0:11:07.00,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,I was able to acquire \Nthe Hero and Thief jobs.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.01,0:11:06.26,Onscreen_Text,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(320,120)\shad0\1a&H20}Villager: Lv 1
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.01,0:11:06.26,Onscreen_Text,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(320,232)\shad0\1a&H20}Thief: Lv 1
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.01,0:11:06.26,Onscreen_Text,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(320,345)\shad0\1a&H20}Equipment: Sandals
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.26,0:11:07.39,Onscreen_Text,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(336,55)\shad0\1a&H20&}Meteor Crash
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.26,0:11:07.39,Onscreen_Text,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(336,130)\shad0\1a&H20&}Gamma Ray Burst
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.26,0:11:07.39,Onscreen_Text,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(336,204)\shad0\1a&H20&}Extreme Drop Dead
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.26,0:11:07.39,Onscreen_Text,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(336,278)\shad0\1a&H20&}Self-Destruct
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.26,0:11:07.39,Onscreen_Text,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(336,350)\shad0\1a&H20&\3c&HB8BCB9&\t(365,406,1 \c&H303330&\bord2)}Equivalent Exchange
Dialogue: 1,0:11:07.00,0:11:10.73,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Though the conditions were complex, \NI was even able to acquire the Mage job.
Dialogue: 1,0:11:10.73,0:11:14.10,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,It's hard to believe the \NBlacksmith job alone is innate.
Dialogue: 1,0:11:14.10,0:11:17.07,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,How is a dwarf's aptitude measured, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.52,0:11:17.07,Onscreen_Text,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an4\pos(20,180)\fs16\fsp0\3c&H4B4E4B&\bord2\shad0\1a&H20}Mage: Lv 1\NEffect: Minor Intelligence Increase\NEffect: Tiny MP Increase\NSkill: Novice Level Fire Magic\NSkill: Novice Level Water Magic\NSkill: Novice Level Air Magic\NSkill: Novice Level Earth Magic
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.71,0:11:19.02,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Can I ask you something?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.02,0:11:20.45,Main,SHERRY,0000,0000,0000,,Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.01,0:11:23.62,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Once you fail to become a Blacksmith,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.62,0:11:25.95,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,is it impossible to become \None in the future?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.86,0:11:31.92,Main,SHERRY,0000,0000,0000,,The Blacksmiths Guild only allows \Nlevel ten Explorers to change jobs.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.37,0:11:35.92,Main,SHERRY,0000,0000,0000,,It's not as though there \Nare no prior examples,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.92,0:11:38.76,Main,SHERRY,0000,0000,0000,,but I don't know exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.76,0:11:40.17,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.56,0:11:42.76,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,It sounds like becoming \Na Blacksmith has conditions
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.76,0:11:45.87,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,other than just being a level ten Explorer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.87,0:11:51.11,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Are they abstract and difficult \Nconditions to meet like aptitude?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.11,0:11:52.83,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,As long as she can fulfill those,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.83,0:11:55.49,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,even this girl should be able \Nto acquire the Blacksmith job.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.69,0:12:01.70,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,And it'd be a waste to turn her away \Njust because she's not a Blacksmith.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.70,0:12:05.01,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,She's exactly the type of person I'd \Nwant for my second party member.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.01,0:12:08.35,Main,SHERRY,0000,0000,0000,,I was one of the strongest \Npeople in my village.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.35,0:12:10.89,Main,SHERRY,0000,0000,0000,,I'm tall for a dwarf,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.89,0:12:13.52,Main,SHERRY,0000,0000,0000,,and I won't cause you any \Ntrouble in labyrinths.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.52,0:12:15.58,Main,SHERRY,0000,0000,0000,,I hope you'll take that into consideration.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.79,0:12:23.34,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, Roxanne was the same, but why?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.34,0:12:25.76,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,Are you finished?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.76,0:12:27.84,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.84,0:12:29.22,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.52,0:12:43.26,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Why is she so assertive?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.26,0:12:47.03,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,If I were a slave, I doubt I'd \Ntry so hard to sell myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.03,0:12:48.99,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's because it's a good deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.29,0:12:50.04,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.62,0:12:53.64,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,She'd be going into dangerous labyrinths.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.64,0:12:56.20,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,She's either been to them before
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.20,0:12:58.50,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,or is planning on entering them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.50,0:13:00.36,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,I certainly did.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.92,0:13:05.42,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think that dwarf seems promising?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.08,0:13:07.64,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.64,0:13:10.24,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know much about dwarves,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.24,0:13:12.82,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,but even if she lacks aptitude, \Nas long as she has the resolve,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.82,0:13:15.52,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,then she'll manage with \Nhard work and training.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.52,0:13:16.77,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.77,0:13:20.23,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,So she's not opposed to the idea \Njust because she's a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.23,0:13:23.99,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,But I doubt she'll be able \Nto do much for very long.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.41,0:13:26.50,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,That's probably why she's not expensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.50,0:13:28.68,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,I think she'd be a good purchase.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.68,0:13:30.40,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.40,0:13:33.18,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Why wouldn't she be able \Nto do much for very long?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.18,0:13:36.50,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,She must be of a certain age.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.83,0:13:39.63,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps we should get confirmation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.59,0:13:43.09,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.09,0:13:46.15,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Sherry was definitely 16 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.15,0:13:47.34,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,It's her ears.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.34,0:13:48.39,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Her ears?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.39,0:13:51.72,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Dwarves' ears get thinner with age.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.06,0:13:55.27,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Hers are rather thin, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.27,0:13:57.79,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Is that how it works?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.26,0:14:02.23,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.96,0:14:10.11,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Would it be all right if I excused \Nmyself for a moment? She...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.11,0:14:11.77,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,She took care of you, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.77,0:14:13.45,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Go talk to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.45,0:14:14.91,Main,ROXANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.09,0:14:24.80,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, what did you think of Sherry?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.80,0:14:27.84,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Well, depending on the price, \Nshe might not be a bad pickup.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.84,0:14:29.63,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.94,0:14:32.56,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sherry may not be a Blacksmith,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.56,0:14:34.04,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,but she's a 16-year-old dwarf.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.04,0:14:37.19,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,She understands that she'll be a sex slave.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.19,0:14:40.77,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,Since she's a virgin, \Nyou needn't worry about diseases.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.77,0:14:42.04,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.04,0:14:43.40,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,I get it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.40,0:14:47.32,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,He had Roxanne excuse herself \Nso he could tell me this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.90,0:14:49.65,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Her ears seemed a bit thin.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.65,0:14:54.12,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed. But she was born that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.12,0:14:57.80,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,I can guarantee Sherry is 16 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.80,0:15:00.68,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,That doesn't change the \Nfact that they're thin.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.68,0:15:03.62,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, her price can \Nbe reduced accordingly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.62,0:15:06.38,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,How does 300 thousand nars sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.63,0:15:10.02,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,Rather, I wish I could charge that much,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.02,0:15:11.50,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,but she hasn't been here long.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.50,0:15:15.16,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,Her training is lacking in some areas,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.16,0:15:16.97,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,so how about 270 thousand nars?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.27,0:15:20.23,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,That's way cheaper than the 600 \Nthousand he charged for Roxanne.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.23,0:15:22.52,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,But I can't jump at this price.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.42,0:15:25.97,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then 260 thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.97,0:15:27.44,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,He dropped the price.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.44,0:15:29.63,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,No, 250 thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.63,0:15:31.87,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's the lowest I can go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.87,0:15:35.37,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,He must be hoping to sell her now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.37,0:15:37.06,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Then, I'll push a little harder.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.06,0:15:38.54,Main,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,That much?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.92,0:15:41.79,Main,ALAN,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.02,0:15:44.84,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? He can't go any lower, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.84,0:15:47.05,Italics,MICHIO,0000,0000,0000,,But I've still got a card up my sleeve.
